Get filtered matches

get_filtered_matches.Rd

Get filtered matches

Usage

get_filtered_matches(
  data,
  treatment,
  covariates,
  id = NULL,
  weight = "wt",
  ind_categorical = NULL
)

Arguments

data

Data frame.

treatment

Character. Name of the treatment column in data. Currently assumes 1 for treatment and 0 for control.

covariates

Character vector. Vector of covariate column names from data to use in match

id

Character. Name of the id column in data

weight

Character. The name that should be given to the variable containing the weights in the output data frame. Default is "wt".

ind_categorical

Logical vector. (Optional) Indicator of which . covariates are categorical.

Value

A data frame of filtered matches

Examples

get_filtered_matches(
  example_trial_data,
  treatment = "Z",
  covariates = c("age", "stage4", "site", "ecog", "prevTrt", "diseaseFree")
)
